Question: Write a program to declare and initialize variables of different data types (integer, floating-point, string) in your chosen programming language.

Solution: 

#include <iostream>
#include<string>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
   int intVar = 10;
   
   float floatVar = 10.02;
   
   string strVar = "Macky's Tech!";
   
   cout<<"integer value: "<<intVar<<endl;
   cout<<"float value: "<<floatVar<<endl;
   cout<<"string value: "<<strVar<<endl;

    return 0;
}


Output:

integer value: 10
float value: 10.02
string value: Macky's Tech!


Thank You!

